modules.description: Performs iterative refinement of cluster centers by reassigning points to the nearest center and recalculating centers based on assigned points. Operates on lists of numerical vectors and associated cluster labels. Used to optimize groupings in datasets where cluster centroids evolve through repeated updates.

Iterates over elements of a list or array, applying a given function to each element with approximate timing measurements. Operates on lists and arrays of arbitrary elements. Useful for profiling the performance of element-wise processing in data-intensive applications.
